r, which doesn't have the ProjectBuilder. Could it rely on local Gradle unit fixtures? I can't find a published `org.gradle:gradle-tooling-api`, but I know `ProjectBuilder` is in `org.gradle:gradle-core`. Actually, it seems to be in the Gradle 9 unit-test-fixtures jar. The Gradle documentation mentions using `testImplementation gradleTestKit()` for custom plugin tests, so I need to check if gradleTestKit() includes the necessary fixtures. But hmm, if my build isn't currently a Gradle plugin, I might need to rethink how I access dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing Gradle modifications**\\n\\nI'm contemplating whether to check the `build/classes` of the placeholder with CheckedRunnable to see if the previous source used some helper, but it doesn't seem like it did. I could potentially use Groovy for a task instantiation, although the ProjectBuilder is still absent. User says to modify only the test file and adjust `build.gradle` if absolutely necessary. It’s a tricky situation since I know the ProjectBuilder is likely missing; however, creating a Gradle project requires updates to the build file. So, I’ll have to weigh these options carefully before proceeding.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_swZduHb7VPVyL6Y6Dmkf9xDm|fc_001c9f44544a01750169fe09cfea788191a09b5967fa96222e", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sf.proguard/proguard-gradle/5.2.1/src/test/java/net_sf_proguard/proguard_gradle/Proguard_gradleTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "package net_sf_proguard.proguard_gradle;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nclass Proguard_gradleTest {\n    @Test\n    void test() throws Exception {\n        System.out.println(\"This is just a placeholder, implement your test\");\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "package net_sf_proguard.proguard_gradle;\n\nimport org.gradle.api.Project;\nimport org.gradle.testfixtures.ProjectBuilder;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Timeout;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\nimport proguard.gradle.ProGuardTask;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.LinkedHashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class Proguard_gradleTest {\n\n    @TempDir\n    Path temporaryDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    @Timeout(60)\n    void proGuardTaskDslTracksProgramLibraryAndConfigurationFiles() throws Exception {\n        final Project project = ProjectBuilder.builder()\n                .withProjectDir(temporaryDirectory.toFile())\n                .build();\n        final ProGuardTask task = project.getTasks().create(\"minifyApplication\", ProGuardTask.class);\n        final File firstInputJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"application.jar\").toFile();\n        final File secondInputJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"support.jar\").toFile();\n        final File outputJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"application-minified.jar\").toFile();\n        final File libraryJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"runtime.jar\").toFile();\n        final File configurationFile = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"proguard.pro\").toFile();\n        final Map<String, String> inputFilters = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        inputFilters.put(\"filter\", \"!META-INF/**\");\n        inputFilters.put(\"jarfilter\", \"**.class\");\n        final Map<String, String> outputFilters = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        outputFilters.put(\"filter\", \"**.class\");\n        final Map<String, String> libraryFilters = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        libraryFilters.put(\"zipfilter\", \"**.class\");\n\n        task.injars(firstInputJar);\n        task.injars(inputFilters, secondInputJar);\n        task.outjars(outputFilters, outputJar);\n        task.libraryjars(libraryFilters, libraryJar);\n        task.configuration(configurationFile);\n\n        assertThat(task.getInJarFiles()).containsExactly(firstInputJar, secondInputJar);\n        assertThat(task.getInJarFilters()).containsExactly(null, inputFilters);\n        assertThat(task.getOutJarFiles()).containsExactly(outputJar);\n        assertThat(task.getOutJarFilters()).containsExactly(outputFilters);\n        assertThat(task.getInJarCounts()).containsExactly(2);\n        assertThat(task.getLibraryJarFiles()).containsExactly(libraryJar);\n        assertThat(task.getLibraryJarFilters()).containsExactly(libraryFilters);\n        assertThat(task.getConfigurationFiles()).containsExactly(configurationFile);\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 590, "output": 1721, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40711, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778256309141, "responseId": "resp_001c9f44544a01750169fe09b759308191a2239647405db120"}}
[tool-exec] start id=call_swZduHb7VPVyL6Y6Dmkf9xDm|fc_001c9f44544a01750169fe09cfea788191a09b5967fa96222e name=edit args={"path": "tests/src/net.sf.proguard/proguard-gradle/5.2.1/src/test/java/net_sf_proguard/proguard_gradle/Proguard_gradleTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "package net_sf_proguard.proguard_gradle;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nclass Proguard_gradleTest {\n    @Test\n    void test() throws Exception {\n        System.out.println(\"This is just a placeholder, implement your test\");\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "package net_sf_proguard.proguard_gradle;\n\nimport org.gradle.api.Project;\nimport org.gradle.testfixtures.ProjectBuilder;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Timeout;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\nimport proguard.gradle.ProGuardTask;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.LinkedHashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class Proguard_gradleTest {\n\n    @TempDir\n    Path temporaryDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    @Timeout(60)\n    void proGuardTaskDslTracksProgramLibraryAndConfigurationFiles() throws Exception {\n        final Project project = ProjectBuilder.builder()\n                .withProjectDir(temporaryDirectory.toFile())\n                .build();\n        final ProGuardTask task = project.getTasks().create(\"minifyApplication\", ProGuardTask.class);\n        final File firstInputJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"application.jar\").toFile();\n        final File secondInputJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"support.jar\").toFile();\n        final File outputJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"application-minified.jar\").toFile();\n        final File libraryJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"runtime.jar\").toFile();\n        final File configurationFile = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"proguard.pro\").toFile();\n        final Map<String, String> inputFilters = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        inputFilters.put(\"filter\", \"!META-INF/**\");\n        inputFilters.put(\"jarfilter\", \"**.class\");\n        final Map<String, String> outputFilters = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        outputFilters.put(\"filter\", \"**.class\");\n        final Map<String, String> libraryFilters = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        libraryFilters.put(\"zipfilter\", \"**.class\");\n\n        task.injars(firstInputJar);\n        task.injars(inputFilters, secondInputJar);\n        task.outjars(outputFilters, outputJar);\n        task.libraryjars(libraryFilters, libraryJar);\n        task.configuration(configurationFile);\n\n        assertThat(task.getInJarFiles()).containsExactly(firstInputJar, secondInputJar);\n        assertThat(task.getInJarFilters()).containsExactly(null, inputFilters);\n        assertThat(task.getOutJarFiles()).containsExactly(outputJar);\n        assertThat(task.getOutJarFilters()).containsExactly(outputFilters);\n        assertThat(task.getInJarCounts()).containsExactly(2);\n        assertThat(task.getLibraryJarFiles()).containsExactly(libraryJar);\n        assertThat(task.getLibraryJarFilters()).containsExactly(libraryFilters);\n        assertThat(task.getConfigurationFiles()).containsExactly(configurationFile);\n    }\n}\n"}]}
